Go down to the stationary store and get a bottle of Expo Dry Erase Board
cleaner.  That's what I used to take Sharpie marker off off of my bus.  It
didn't bother the paint at all.  Spray it on, give it a few seconds to
work, and then wipe off with a soft cloth.  Repeat if needed.

George Lyle
